latestPosts.caption:
This is a partial dump from the past couple of months, since I didn’t really feel up to posting these before. I click things, intend to share them, and then one of two things happen:
I feel too overwhelmed and mentally drained to actually sit and make an actual post OR I hate how it looks, I look, question why anyone would even care and let it sit in my drafts. 

I’m realising more and more that as much as this account is about me and Urdu, it is slowly becoming a place where you can see how tricky it is to have chronic anxiety and be a creator/creative. It’s so hard to put yourself out there, when your brain has already convinced you that you are no good and no one really cares.

But of course, for every bad day and bad thought, there are multiple good days and good thoughts. I just need to hold on to those more.❤️

latestPosts.caption:
The third hack to get back to reading for me was reading TV and film scripts—Fleabag pulled me back in when books felt like a chore.

There was something about knowing the voice, the rhythm, the visuals—that made the words easier to stay with. (The other two hacks? In the video.)

But on this World Book Day, here’s a gentle reminder:
It’s okay to relearn how to love something that once came easy.
Even if you start with just one paragraph instead of a whole chapter.
